         <abstract>
            <p>An approach is developed which can aid an acquiring firm's management in its analysis of the desirability of a proposed merger. That approach exploits, from a different perspective than in the prior literature, the price-setting function of the capital marketplace. Issues of the economic merit of an acquisition, the bargaining room available to the bidder firm, and the uncertainty that the acquisition will ultimately occur, are addressed in the process.</p>
         </abstract>
